<title>USA: Electronic Retailing in deal with Shaw's.</title>
<headline>Electronic Retailing in deal with Shaw's.</headline>
<dateline>WILTON, Conn. 1997-07-03</dateline>
<text>
<p>Electronic Retailing Systems International Inc said Thursday Shaw's Supermarkets Inc will add two of its electronic shelf label systems in each of the Clinton and Fairfield, Conn. stores.</p>
<p>The company did not disclose financial details of the deals.</p>
<p>The systems are called ERS ShelfNet.</p>
<p>Shaw's is a wholly-owned subsidiary of J. Sainsbury PLC a food retailer in Britain.</p>
<p>ERS makes and supplies electronic shelf labeling systems designed to improve retailers productivity.</p>
</text>
